@startuml logical_erd_user_roles
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor #1a5ad7
  FontColor #0b2147
  FontSize 12
}

title Logical ERD - User and Roles

entity "User" as user {
  * username : VARCHAR
}

entity "UserRole" as user_role {
  * id : INTEGER
  --
  * username : VARCHAR (FK)
  * role_type : ENUM
  warehouse : VARCHAR
  region : VARCHAR
}

user ||--o{ user_role : "has multiple roles"

note right of user_role
  **Role Types:**
  - admin (no constraints)
  - warehouse_manager (requires region)
  - store_owner (requires warehouse)

  **Constraints:**
  - User can have multiple roles
  - Each role scoped to warehouse OR region
  - Unique per (username, role_type, warehouse)
  - Unique per (username, role_type, region)

  **Examples:**
  - Alice: warehouse_manager for region "West"
  - Alice: store_owner for warehouse "LAX-01"
  - Bob: admin (no scope restrictions)
end note

@enduml
